# Kairox ŌĆö Cursor Rules

## Project
Kairox is a local-first AI agent workbench: Rust workspace core + Tauri/Vue GUI + ratatui TUI, with native skills and plugins.

## Quick commands
- Format check: `just fmt-check` or `bun run format:check`
- Lint: `just lint` or `bun run lint`
- Test: `just test` or `cargo test --workspace --all-targets`
- Full CI gate: `just check`
- Type sync check: `just check-types`
- Desktop E2E: `just test-pilot`
- Live model smoke: `just test-live`
- Run TUI: `just tui`
- Run GUI dev: `just gui-dev`
- Bump version: `just bump-version X.Y.Z`

## Language & tooling
- Rust workspace (edition 2021, resolver 2) + Vue 3 + TypeScript
- Package manager: **Bun only** (never npm, pnpm, or yarn)
- Lint: `cargo clippy -D warnings`, oxlint, Stylelint
- Format: `cargo fmt`, oxfmt

## Crate structure & dependency direction
- agent-core ŌåÉ agent-runtime ŌåÉ agent-tui / agent-gui / agent-eval
- agent-core ŌåÉ agent-store, agent-memory, agent-models, agent-tools, agent-config, agent-mcp, agent-skills
- agent-tools ŌåÆ agent-mcp (re-exports `McpServerDef`, `McpTransportDef`; provides `McpToolAdapter`)
- agent-tools owns the `PolicyEngine` (orthogonal `ApprovalPolicy` ├Ś `SandboxPolicy`); legacy `PermissionMode` is removed
- agent-runtime owns session execution via `SessionActor` (`execution_runtime/`) with race-free turn-end compaction
- agent-skills provides the native skills system for reusable prompt/tool/workflow capabilities
- agent-plugins parses plugin manifests and inventories for plugin-provided skills, tools, hooks, and MCP servers
- agent-config supports `.kairox/` project-level config discovery
- agent-eval is a headless evaluation harness (binary `kairox-eval`)
- agent-runtime ŌåÆ agent-memory, agent-store, agent-models, agent-tools, agent-config, agent-mcp
- Never create reverse dependencies. New domain types/events go in agent-core first.

## Key patterns
- Workspace version: all crates use `version.workspace = true` ŌĆö never set version in individual crate Cargo.toml
- Error handling: each crate has `XxxError` enum via `thiserror::Error` and `type Result<T>`
- Trait boundaries: `AppFacade`, `ModelClient`, `MemoryStore`, `EventStore`, `Tool`, `Transport`, `AgentStrategy` ŌĆö use `Arc<dyn Trait>` or generics
- Context management: model metadata drives context windows; runtime budget assembly, compaction, model switching, and reasoning effort selection must remain consistent across Rust and GUI state
- Async: Tokio + `async_trait`
- Testing: `FakeModelClient` for runtime, in-memory SQLite for stores, tauri-pilot for real desktop E2E, and `live-model-tests` for gated provider smoke coverage
- Tauri IPC: `#[tauri::command]` in `commands.rs` ŌåÆ Vue `invoke()` ŌåÆ events via `event_forwarder.rs` + `useTauriEvents.ts` (filters by session)
- When adding Rust `EventPayload` variants or command/domain types, run `just gen-types`; do not manually edit generated bindings

## Vue conventions
- Vue 3 Composition API (`<script setup lang="ts">`)
- Pinia stores: `apps/agent-gui/src/stores/`
- Composables: `apps/agent-gui/src/composables/`
- Types: `apps/agent-gui/src/types/`

## Commit format
Conventional Commits with scopes: core, runtime, models, tools, memory, store, config, mcp, skills, plugins, eval, tui, gui, docs, deps, ci

## Version bump files (must stay in sync)
1. Cargo.toml (workspace.package.version)
2. Cargo.lock (run `cargo generate-lockfile`)
3. apps/agent-gui/package.json
4. apps/agent-gui/src-tauri/tauri.conf.json
5. package.json (root)

## Common mistakes to avoid
- Using `npm`, `pnpm`, or `yarn` instead of Bun
- Setting `version` in individual crate Cargo.toml
- Hardcoding API keys (use agent-config's `api_key_env`)
- Forgetting to run `just gen-types` when changing Rust events, commands, or generated TypeScript bindings
- Forgetting to register new Tauri commands in both `generate_handler!` (invocation) and `collect_commands!` (specta type-gen)
- Skipping `bun install` after creating a git worktree
- Editing `apps/agent-gui/src/generated/{commands,events}.ts` by hand ŌĆö these are auto-generated, run `just gen-types`
- Forgetting to update `apps/agent-gui/e2e/tauri-mock.js` when adding new `#[tauri::command]` or events
